      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THEO THE GREAT (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing eighth (24.00) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Won at his only start from this draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SUPER QUALITY (4) turned in a plain effort last time when fifth at Gosford over 388m behind Long Dark Road (22.91) in a Grade 5. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Should be in this for a long way. SNIDELY WHIPLASH (2) goes very well at the course with two wins and a placing from five starts. Was out of placings last time (20.29) at Gunnedah in a Grade 5, finishing seventh and beaten 9 lengths. Looks suited here and can measure up. ZIPPING BERKELEY (7) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
